Q1 What is EC2 (Elastic Compute Cloud)?

An EC2 Instance is a virtual server in the cloud provided by Amazon Web Services through the service Amazon EC2 (Elastic Compute Cloud).
It allows you to run applications, host websites, or run backend servers without buying physical hardware.

Operating systems (Linux, Ubuntu, Windows)
Software (Node.js, Java, Python, databases)
Your backend or frontend applications

Example (Real-Time Scenario)
Suppose you build a Node.js backend API.
Instead of running it on your local laptop, you:
Create an EC2 instance on AWS
Install Node.js
Upload your application code
Start the server

Now your API becomes accessible on the internet.
Example URL:
http://3.120.45.10:3000/api/users

